ca.ualberta.cmput301f14t16.easya.Model

Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.ualberta.cmput301f14t16.easya.Model.User

  • public class User
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides a method of storing and accessing all data relevant to a single user, uniquely identified by the id field.

      • User

        public User(java.lang.String email,
            java.lang.String username)
        Creates a new User object associated to the given email and username. id is automatically generated by calling UUID.randomUUID().
        Parameters:
        email - Setter for email.
        username - Setter for username. If an empty string is passed, a random username will be generated using generateNewUserName().

      • generateNewUserName

        private java.lang.String generateNewUserName()
        Creates a random username. The username will take the format of a random word selected from a list, followed by a random number from 1000 to 9999. The list of possible words is as follows: [Guest, Greenhorn, Inquirer, Newcomer, Newbie, Guest]
        Returns:
        a String containing the randomly generated username.
